author: The Virginian-Pilot
title: Friday night's other football games
text:
Games begin at 7 p.m. at the home school unless noted. The schedule is expected to change, so check 757teamz.com Friday for updates. No. 1 Ocean Lakes vs. Kempsville
Site: Virginia Beach Sportsplex
Records: Ocean Lakes 4-0; Kempsville 0-4.
Fast fact: Dolphins head coach Chris Scott is scheduled to return from suspension after this game.
Larry: Ocean Lakes, 49-0. Jami: Ocean Lakes, 48-7.
Nansemond River at No. 4 Indian River
Records: Nansemond River 3-1; Indian River 4-0.
Fast fact: Braves have scored 119 points in past three games.
Larry: Indian River 27-20. Jami: Indian River, 26-12.
No. 9 King's Fork at Great Bridge (postponed to 7 p.m. Monday)
Records: King's Fork 3-1; Great Bridge 0-4.
Fast fact: RB Deshaun Wethington has 480 yards in Bulldogs' past three games.
Larry: King's Fork, 35-0. Jami: King's Fork, 22-8.
Booker T. Washington vs. Churchland (postponed to 7:30 p.m. Monday)
Time: 6 p.m.
Site: Powhatan Field
Records: Booker T. Washington 1-3; Churchland 2-2.
Fast fact: Truckers RB Jamil Edwards rushed for season-high 182 yards in last week's win over Maury.
Larry: Churchland, 23-13. Jami: Churchland, 27-18.
Lakeland at Deep Creek (postponed to 7 p.m. Monday)
Time: 6 p.m.
Records: Lakeland 1-3; Deep Creek 1-3.
Fast fact: Cavaliers picked up first win for new coach Kevin Knight last week.
Larry: Deep Creek, 22-20. Jami: Deep Creek, 14-12.
Maury at Liberty Christian
Time: 4:30 p.m.
Records: Maury 1-3; Liberty Christian 2-3.
Fast fact: Commodores travel to Lynchburg to play Bulldogs in their first season as VHSL member.
Larry: Liberty Christian, 26-23. Jami: Maury, 20-17.
Norcom at Wilson (postponed to 7 p.m. Monday)
Records: Norcom 0-4; Wilson 2-2.
Fast fact: Greyhounds mired in first 0-4 start since 2003, but three losses are by nine or fewer points.
Larry: Norcom, 20-16. Jami: Wilson, 13-10.
